INSERT INTO tutor (name, company, bio, created, updated) VALUES ('Vickie Griffin','VMG Training','Vickie works with Fitch Learning to create, develop and deliver technical and professional skills training to a wide range of banking, asset management and wealth management clients.  Until 2013 she was a Private Banker for Barclays and provided cash, banking, investment and wealth planning advice to clients with net wealth of up to Â£50m. She is credit qualified and provided mortgage and other credit led advice to Barclays Private Bank clients.  Her background prior to Private banking includes a long tenure at Grant Thornton where she provided capital taxes and investment advice to a range of clients including a Â£35m employee benefit trust and a number of families appearing on the Sunday Times Rich List. Vickie has a Law degree from the University of Sheffield and is a qualified Chartered Accountant and Chartered Tax Adviser.  She holds a number of financial services qualifications including the PCIAM qualification in which she attained a distinction in 2012.    Industry Experience Vickie has over 15 yearsâ€™ experience in financial related services. She began her career in accountancy, where she gained a broad knowledge on managing businesses as well as advising entrepreneurial clients.  Vickie progressed to managing private client relationships having gained her tax adviser, investment management and credit advisor qualifications.  Her final role within the industry was as a Private Banker with Barclays where she managed clients with net wealth of Â£1m to Â£30m. Training Experience Vickie returned to training 2 years ago and has worked with graduates, new starters, and operations staff at all levels, helping them to understand the many complex concepts that exist within the financial markets. She delivers tailored financial markets training and professional qualifications as well as personal development training on client service and relationship management. At Fitc